XcelCrowd API Documentation (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:Download

XcelCrowd Support: support@xcelcrowd.com URL: https://xcelcrowd.com/support License: Proprietary

API documentation for XcelCrowd platform - A student-only platform connecting university talent with industry challenges. This platform enables students to build professional profiles, engage with company challenges, and receive professional feedback.

Authentication

API endpoints for user authentication and authorization

Logout current user

Invalidates the current session and clears authentication cookies

Authorizations:
bearerAuth

Responses

API Server

http://localhost:5000/api/auth/logout

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
Content type
application/json
{
  • "success": true,
  • "message": "Logged out successfully",
  • "data": null,
  • "timestamp": "2023-05-26T14:45:00.000Z"
}

Register a new student account

Creates a new student user account and profile. Validates email and password requirements.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
email
required
string <email>

Student's email address (must be a valid academic email)

password
required
string <password> >= 8 characters

Strong password (min 8 chars with uppercase, lowercase, number, and special char)

firstName
required
string

Student's first name

lastName
required
string

Student's last name

university
string

Academic institution name

Responses

API Server

http://localhost:5000/api/auth/student/register

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "email": "student@university.edu",
  • "password": "StrongP@ss123",
  • "firstName": "John",
  • "lastName": "Smith",
  • "university": "Oxford University"
}

Response samples

  • 201
  • 400
  • 409
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "success": true,
  • "message": "Registration successful",
  • "data": {
    • "user": {
      • "_id": "60d21b4667d0d8992e610c85",
      • "email": "user@example.com",
      • "role": "student"
      },
    • "profile": { },
    • "csrfToken": "a1b2c3d4e5f6..."
    },
  • "timestamp": "2023-05-26T14:45:00.000Z"
}

Authenticate student and get token

Validates student credentials and returns JWT token for authentication. The token is also set as an HTTP-only cookie.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
email
required
string <email>

User's email address

password
required
string <password> >= 8 characters

User's password

Responses

API Server

http://localhost:5000/api/auth/student/login

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "email": "user@example.com",
  • "password": "Password123!"
}

  • 400
  • 401
  • 429
  • 500

Users

User management operations

Get all users with pagination and filtering

Retrieves a paginated list of users. Restricted to admin users only.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
query Parameters
page
integer >= 1
Default: 1

Page number

limit
integer [ 1 .. 100 ]
Default: 10

Number of items per page

sort
string
Example: sort=createdAt:desc

Sort field and direction (field:asc|desc)

email
string

Filter by email (partial match)

role
string (UserRole)
Enum: "student" "company" "architect" "admin"
Example: role=student

Filter by user role

Responses

API Server

http://localhost:5000/api/users

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 403
  • 500
Content type
application/json
{
  • "success": true,
  • "message": "Users retrieved successfully",
  • "data": [
    • {
      • "_id": "60d21b4667d0d8992e610c85",
      • "email": "user@example.com",
      • "role": "student",
      • "isEmailVerified": false,
      • "createdAt": "2023-05-20T14:20:30.000Z",
      • "updatedAt": "2023-05-20T14:20:30.000Z"
      }
    ],
  • "metadata": {
    • "pagination": {
      • "page": 1,
      • "limit": 10,
      • "total": 100,
      • "totalPages": 10
      }
    },
  • "timestamp": "2023-05-26T14:45:00.000Z",
  • "requestId": "1a2b3c4d-5e6f-7g8h-9i0j"
}

Challenges

Operations for managing company challenges

Create a new challenge

Creates a new challenge. Available only to company users.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
Request Body schema: application/json
required
title
required
string <= 100 characters

Challenge title

description
required
string

Detailed challenge description

requirements
required
Array of strings

Specific requirements for solution submissions

resources
Array of strings

Resources provided to help with the challenge

rewards
string

Details about prizes or compensation

deadline
required
string <date-time>

Submission deadline

difficulty
required
string (ChallengeDifficulty)
Enum: "beginner" "intermediate" "advanced" "expert"

Difficulty level of a challenge

category
required
Array of strings

Categories the challenge belongs to

maxParticipants
integer >= 1

Maximum allowed number of participants

tags
Array of strings

Keywords or tags associated with the challenge

maxApprovedSolutions
integer >= 1

Maximum number of solutions that can be approved

visibility
string (ChallengeVisibility)
Enum: "public" "private" "anonymous"

Visibility setting of a challenge

allowedInstitutions
Array of strings

List of institutions that can see private challenges (required for private visibility)

isCompanyVisible
boolean

Whether company identity is shown (default is true unless visibility is anonymous)

Responses

API Server

http://localhost:5000/api/challenges

Get all challenges

Retrieves a list of challenges with optional filtering. Accessible to all authenticated users.

Authorizations:
bearerAuth
query Parameters
page
integer >= 1
Default: 1

Page number

limit
integer [ 1 .. 100 ]
Default: 10

Number of items per page

sort
string
Example: sort=createdAt:desc

Sort field and direction (field:asc|desc)

status
string (ChallengeStatus)
Enum: "draft" "active" "closed" "completed"
Example: status=active

Filter by challenge status

category
string

Filter by category

difficulty
string (ChallengeDifficulty)
Enum: "beginner" "intermediate" "advanced" "expert"
Example: difficulty=intermediate

Filter by difficulty

skills
string

Comma-separated list of skills to filter by

search
string

Search term for challenge title or description
